DIV2.P:
As Children are virtually in their Parents before they are begotten and born into the World, so it hath pleased GOD to include Pa∣rents together with their Children in the Cove∣nant. Thus it was under the first Covenant, the Covenant of Works made with Adam, "not for himself only, but for his Posterity". And thus it is under the New Covenant, the Covenant of Grace. GOD promised Abraham, Gen. 17.7. I will establish my covenant be∣tween me and thee, and thy seed after thee, in their generations for an everlasting covenant;


to be a God unto thee, and to thy seed after thee. Which blessing is come on the believing Gentiles thro' JESUS CHRIST, Gal. 3.14. Let Parents then under the realizing view of the frailty of this life, make hast to lay hold of GOD's Covenant, and to give up themselves and their Seed to Him as their GOD, and that with their whole hearts; that whatever changes pass over your Houses, you may rejoyce with David, 2 Sam. 23.5. Although my house be not so with God; yet he hath made with me in everlasting covenant, ordered in all things and sure: for this is all my salvation, and all my desire, although he make it not to grow. In this way, devote them to GOD, that He may own them as His Children, and take them up when you forsake them: In this way, bring them to CHRIST for His blessing, who said, Suffer little Children, and forbid them not to come unto me: for of such is the kingdom of heaven, Mat. 19.14. In this way, seek to GOD that they may be Saved by the washing of Regeneration, and the renewing of the Holy Ghost. Indeed, we can't say that all who are visibly in Covenant obtain the invisible Grace and saving Blessings of the Covenant: For they are not all Israel, which are of Israel, Rom. 9.6. Sad experience teach∣eth us that not a few have with profane Esau despised the Birth-right. However, this is one of the means of Grace which that GOD hath appointed who alone can command the Blessing; and the consideration of the uncertainty of our own lives as well as the lives of our Children,


should make us speedy and very serious in this Covenant transaction with GOD on their be∣half, that we may in faith plead the Promises of GOD's Covenant for them, when we are a∣bout to be taken from them.
